The assembler is a powered machine which crafts items, it can be upgraded by inserting Acceleration Cards into it; once upgraded it is very fast.
Uses the Encoded Patterns (must be a crafting recipe)  from attached ME Interface to craft items when they are requested by the Crafting CPU.
Allows you to configure which users, and what permissions the users have with the ME System. By existing it enforces permissions on the usage of the system.
Access your system wirelessvia a Wireless Terminal
Craft from anywhere you like, provided that you have an infinity booster upgrade.
The Solderer is a block that is used to craft several items from the mod

The Disk Drive is a block that has one goal: provide storage to the system.

You can insert storage disks or fluid storage disks in the inventory slots and those disks will be used to put the items or fluids on.

The Controller is the block every Refined Storage system will need. It is the core of your system.
You are supposed to connect every device that depends on a storage network connection to the Controller.

You can connect devices by connecting Cable to them.

Cables are not always necessary, as long as the devices are next to each other in any direction a connection will be established as well.

The Crafter is a block that crafts items with patterns. It can take speed upgrades to increase the crafting speed.

With patterns meant for machine automation, the Crafter has to face the correct input side of the machine.

The Security Manager is a block that can store security cards.

From it's GUI, you can configure what permissions each player (that is bound with a Security Card) has.

Once the Security Card is inserted into the top slots, the permissions for that player will be restricted to the ones configured.
Processor is used to craft the various Refined Storage devices.
The 1k Storage Disk can store 1.000 items.
The 1k Storage Disk can store 4.000 items.
The 16k Storage Disk can store 16.000 items.
The 64k Storage Disk can store 64.000 items.
The Crafting Grid is the same as a regular Grid, but has a crafting inventory too.

With the Wireless Grid the player can access their items from anywhere.

To activate the Wireless Grid, the player has to right click the Wireless Grid on a Controller.

Gem armor is more offensive and offers flight. It is made by combining different Power Items with Red Matter Armour, most notably the Klein Star Omega which you need for every recipe.
